'''BLC Leather Technology Centre''' or '''BLC''' is a testing, auditing and consulting business that specialises in chemicals, leather, footwear and other associated products and related materials, and is based in [[Northamptonshire]] <ref>[https://www.blcleathertech.com/about-us]</ref><ref>[http://www.laboratory-directory.com/contract-laboratories/profile/blc-leather-technology-centre-ltd]</ref>. An additional specialism is the safe use and management of chemicals in the supply chain; a concept from which BLC developed the ZDHC approved BLC Chem-MAP certification process for chemicals, chemical companies, brands and their suppliers<ref>[https://www.chem-map.com/]</ref><ref>[https://www.roadmaptozero.com/news/post/zdhc-announces-blc-chem-map-as-zdhc-accepted-certification-standard/]</ref>.
A significant item of note is that BLC is the official facilitator of the Leather Working Group (LWG) which is a significant environmental stewardship programme within the leather industry. The LWG has over 600 member companies that includes over 100 major clothing and footwear brands<ref>[https://www.leatherworkinggroup.com/]</ref>.
==BLC==
In March 2018, BLC was acquired by [[Eurofins Scientific]] of [[Belgium]] who now have a majority share holding in the company.<ref>[https://www.eurofins.com/consumer-product-testing/media-centre/news/blc-leather-technology-centre-ltd-joins-eurofins/ Eurofins]</ref>.
